                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-11T18:00:00+01:20"
                            >September 11, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 12—7:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>169. For the Secretary and Under Secretary. My 167, September 10, 1 p.m.<note
                        n="15" xml:id="d778fn15">Not printed; it reported a meeting of the Belgian
                        and Netherland Foreign Ministers at Breda, September 11, in an endeavor to
                        reach agreement on an identic reply to the British proposal (740.00112
                        European War 1939/40).</note> Dutch and Belgians have agreed on identic
                    note. Conditionally being put before the Oslo States with the suggestion that if
                    they wish they can send a similar note but they are being told that whether they
                    do or not the Dutch and Belgians will send this note in reply to the British
                    proposal. As soon as note is delivered to British I will be given a copy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
